FBIS3-22684 "jptep008___94044" JPRS-TEP-94-008 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Epidemiology 23 March 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Viral Hepatitis Hospitalizes 270 in Sakhalin LD2303092194 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0730 GMT 23 Mar 94 LD2303092194 Moscow 2x2 Television Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] In Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk and some other towns of the island 270 people have been hospitalized with the diagnosis of viral hepatitis. SUVOROVSKIY NATISK, the newspaper of the Far East military district, reports that the jaundice is caused by polluted drinking water. So far no servicemen have fallen ill.
